node.text: I wanted to create a tufted look so I used Turkey work or also called the fringe stitch. You can leave this stitch as loops or cut for a tufted look. I used fingering weight wool yarn, but any threads will work. To give it a more fluffy look take your needle and comb the yarn☺️👌🏼

Lately I've been enjoying using this decorative technique as a way to mend a hole or to create a pattern when I'm collaging with fabric.  I show you how to use this technique with hand sewing, but you can definitely do it with a sewing machine.  I find that lighter weight fabrics work best so there's not so much bulk when you are turning over your edges, but feel free to experiment and do what works best for you.  I hope you enjoy the tutorial and please leave me any questions below😄

node.text: There are a lot of ways to transfer your design for #embroidery and my go to method is to draw directly on the cloth. My second favourite is using sulky’s stick n’ stitch because you can print your image from your home printer and the paper dissolves in water. It’s great for darker base-cloths or if you have a detailed image👍🏼😄

Awhile ago I had my designs woven and I had some fabric left and my mum made pocket pouches for the update. I love it🤩so great to hold notions or for your money and keys👍🏼
The shop update is tomorrow at noon EST- the items will be listed under shop update - I’ll put a swipe up in stories tomorrow.  Thank you for all your kind words on my pillow yesterday 🧡

node.text:
here’s the #punchneedle pillow from yesterday’s reel 🤩 I’m really enjoying these designs that leave the base cloth exposed 👍🏼 I created a black outline so that the shapes popped more. I also like the extended yarn length for the #tufting 😄
This item is available in the originals section of the web shop 🧡

node.text:
Creating a pillow with just the motif punched. I’m working on loose weave linen and using a no. 9 fine and regular. For the centre of the flower I pinched the loops so that they would be longer and I snipped the loops to get a tufted look 🤩🧡
I’ll show you tomorrow the finished #punchneedle piece
